                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4/202a: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in France, Great Britain,
                            Italy, and Japan</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-27T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 27, 1921—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conference on Limitation of Armament. Department’s circular of September 3.<note
                        n="81" xml:id="d90fn81">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_66">p. 66</ref>.</note>
                    President Harding for same reasons expressed therein in case of Belgium and
                    Holland desires now to invite the Portuguese Government to Conference for
                    purpose only of taking part in discussion of Pacific and Far Eastern problems,
                    if the Government to which you are accredited has no objection. Please inquire
                    and cable reply as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
